DataElement.preferredName: Boolean Column Order Value boolean One Dimensional Array
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The type of an expression with two possible values, "true" and "false". Also, a variable of Boolean type or a function with Boolean arguments or result. The most common Boolean functions are AND, OR and NOT.:An arrangement of objects one under another in a line._A logical or comprehensible arrangement of separate elements; a condition of regular or proper arrangement.:A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed._Generic value domain for a single dimensional array with an ordered list of true or false values as elements.
